<p>
  <span class="nym">Baruch</span>
  <span class="gen">m.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">Hebrew</span> <i>בָּרוּךְ</i> 'blessed'.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
<div class="usg">
  <p>The name of a number minor Biblical characters, one of whom was credited with authoring the deuterocanonical Book of Baruch. Wycliffite Bible (1395): <i>Baruch</i>.</p>
</div>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>This name came into use amongst the Protestants in the second half of the 16th century.</p>
  
  


<dl>
<dt><span class="area">France</span></dt>
<dd>
<dl>
<dt><span class="lang">Middle French</span></dt>
<dd><span class="dim">●</span> <span class="date">1565</span> <span class="name">Baruch</span> <a href="../cite/Baruch/1565/RegPCC-1"><span class="bib_key">RegPCC-1</span> <span class="bib_loc">p. 165</span></a></dd>
</dl>
</dd>
</dl>


